u003Cp\u003EThe photograph shows several diverticulae in the colon. Diverticular disease is very common in Western communities, where perhaps more than 60% of patients over the age of 60 have the condition. Increasingly, diverticular disease is being found in younger age groups and it is estimated that more than 20% of cases of diverticulitis occur in patients younger than 50. With the increasing use of CT and colonoscopy, it is not surprising that most cases of diverticular disease are being found \u003Cstrong\u003Eincidentally\u003C/strong\u003E during one of these procedures. Complications of diverticular disease may lead to any of the other four listed situations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diverticular disease is very common and is usually asymptomatic."],"references":["Klarenbeek BR, de Korte N, van der Peet DL, Cuesta MA. Review of current classifications for diverticular disease and a translation into clinical practice. Int J Colorectal Dis. 2012;27(2):207-14. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3267934/#main-content"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52103"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"544"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16859"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16859","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16859"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fc274356-7ba1-421c-b89b-9a7202ef5cc2.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fc274356-7ba1-421c-b89b-9a7202ef5cc2.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":705,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52103"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T17:55:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T17:55:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"544"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66650"}}},"m